### research_assess
Assess findings from research tools with effort/impact/urgency scoring. Pure computation — no HTTP calls. Takes findings from spec, SDK, or ecosystem tools and produces prioritized assessments with recommendations.

Examples:

  Assess a spec gap:
  Input: {"findings": "..."}
  Output: Prioritized assessment with effort=3, impact=5, urgency=4

**Parameters:**
```json
{
  "properties": {
    "findings": {
      "description": "Findings to assess (from spec/sdk/ecosystem tools)",
      "items": {
        "properties": {
          "category": {
            "description": "Category (spec_change/sdk_update/ecosystem/gap)",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": {
            "description": "Details about the finding",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "description": "Name of the finding",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "severity": {
            "description": "low/medium/high/critical",
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "name"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      },
      "type": "array"
    },
    "scoring_weights": {
      "description": "Custom weights for effort/impact/urgency scoring",
      "properties": {
        "effort_weight": {
          "description": "Weight for effort score (default 1.0)",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "impact_weight": {
          "description": "Weight for impact score (default 1.5)",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "urgency_weight": {
          "description": "Weight for urgency score (default 1.2)",
          "type": "number"
        }
      },
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "findings"
  ],
  "type": "object"
}
```

